properties.documentation: The intellectual work to evaluate an asset against the criteria of a given scenario.
The context for a criterion providing guidance on its evaluation considering the given scenario.
The context of the assessment establishing its purpose, the organisation of criteria being evaluated, and its reference frameworks.
The value output assigned to the criterion as part of the assessment.
A value judgement, resulting from the assessment, pertinent to its entirety or to one or more of its specific parts.

documentation.value: The categorisation of the statement.
The favourability perception of the statement (e.g. positive, negative or neutral).
The text expressing the statements resulting value judgement.

properties.documentation: The rule or principle used to judge, evaluate or assess something. The Criterion class has the properties described below.

Agreed, descriptive and reference requirements. Additional information: These requirements usually are issued by organizations that wish to work together towards a similar purpose. One common use of a reference framework is for the derivation of criteria. Examples of Reference Framework may be:
  • Legislation (either european, national or both);
  • A set of principles, recommendations and the structured or organised ideas (e.g. the EIF principles, dimensions and recommendations);
  • A family of specifications and standards.

documentation.value: An abbreviated manifestation of the performed assessment.
The agent(s) that carry out the assessment.
The assignment of the scenario for the current assessment providing its context, purpose and criteria.
Triggers: The event causing further related assessment(s) due to the current one. TriggeredFrom: The event causing the current assessment as the result of another related assessment.
The reference to the asset(s) that are the object of the assessment.

The creation of the statements resulting from the assessment.
Note: This needs to be reviewed urgently.
The evaluation of a criterion score in the context of the current assessment as input to issue one or more statements.

A manifestation of all the information related to and resulting from an assessment. Additional Information:
  • The included information usually contains everything about the assessment, e.g. the purpose of the assessment, the criteria defined in the scenario, the responses and the scoring provided by the evaluator;
  • The report may be manifested in one or multiple ways (distributed as different formats), e.g. as OWL triples, as an HTML, as a narrative text (pdf, doc, ods, etc.).
The agent(s) requesting the assessment of an asset.
The provision of context for the evaluation of the criterion.

definedBy: The link to the scenario that provides the evaluation context for one or more criteria.
defines: The link to the evaluation contexts for specific criteria provided by the given scenario.
The consideration of a specific evaluation context when assigning the score to a criterion.

The aggregation of criteria to one scenario or parts of it.
Additional Information: This aggregation may be contextualised at different granularity levels, scenario, parts of the scenario or specific criteria. The cardinality is 0..* to allow assessments that are very high-level, informal or subjective without criteria and scoring. For CAMSS the cardinality is 1..*.
The provision of a value judgement on one or more elements of the assessment.
The agent assigning the score for a given criterion as part of the assessment.
The assignment of a value output to the criterion.
The provision of a value judgement on one or more elements of the assessment.
The agent(s) that issue value judgement(s) resulting from the assessment.
